FAQ This is also a list of rules and regulations.
  1. Can I add you as a friend?
  2. Do I need to comment when taking an icon?
  3. Do I need to credit you? How?
  4. Can I modify your icons?
  5. Can I hotlink?
  6. Do you take requests?
  7. How can I contact you?
  8. Will you help me with my layout?
  9. How do I affiliate your community?
  10. Can I nominate your icons at award communities?
  11. I commented ages ago, why haven't you replied?
  12. What icon programs do you use?
  13. Where did you get that brush/texture/picture?
  14. How can I see your past icons without going back day by day?
  15. Are icons the only thing you do?
  16. Can I request a tutorial?
  17. Where can I find your affiliates/resources/awards/tutorials?
1. Can I add you as a friend? Yes please! That's how you can view my icons when they are posted. Just click [here] to add me as a friend. However, please don't ask me to add you back as I don't add anyone. Top Of Page 2. Do I need to comment when taking an icon? Absolutely. If I know my icons are liked, I will keep making them. Simple as that. Oh yeah, and all that stuff about knowing where the icons are going and which are the most liked. Yeah, that stuff. Top Of Page 3. Do I need to credit you? How? Yes please! [Here's a tutorial on how] You can credit me as in the icon's keywords. Top Of Page 4. Can I modify your icons? NO, DO NOT MODIFY MY ICONS, especially textless ones. Ask me to do it, at the very least. The only modifying I allow is the resizing of banners to fit layouts etc. I consider adding usernames to icons as modifying. Top Of Page 5. Can I hotlink? ABSOLUTELY NOT. This means save to your own server, don't bum off mine. There is absolutely no reason under the sun why I would allow hotlinking, so just don't do it. Don't know what hotlinking is? [Click Here] Top Of Page 6. Do you take requests? No, sorry. However, I occasionally post inviting people to request. Then and only then can you request. Top Of Page 7. How can I contact you? Comment in any of my posts. This is the ONLY way you can contact me. I do read each and every comment made though I only reply if I need to. Top Of Page 8. Will you help me with my layout? No, sorry. There are communities for that. Top Of Page 9. How do I affiliate your community? I am pretty much constantly accepting affiliates, so comment [here]. It's that easy. Top Of Page 10. Can I nominate your icons at award communities? As if anyone will ever ask this, but go ahead. Top Of Page 11. I commented ages ago, why haven't you replied? Because I'm ignoring you Because I will comment when the mood strikes me or when you ask a question. I don't feel the need to thank people every time they comment so, thanks. Top Of Page 12. What icon programs do you use? Photoshop CS2. Only the best of the best ^_^ Top Of Page 13. Where did you get that brush/texture/picture? Check out my [resource list] or ask me and I will see if I can remember where I got it from. Top Of Page 14. How can I see your past icons without going back day by day? This snazzy new invention called [memories] Top Of Page 15. Are icons the only thing you do? No I also do blends and banners and backgrounds and whatever else tickles my fancy. Top Of Page 16. Can I request a tutorial? I save most of my icons in their .psd files so yes, you may request a tutorial and I will see what I can do. Top Of Page 17. Where can I find your affiliates/resources/awards/tutorials Here's a list of helpful links around my icon journal: [Affiliates] [Resources] [Awards] [Tutorials] Top Of Page If I missed anything, please let me know.
